Creating of LinkedList
https://practice.geeksforgeeks.org/problems/introduction-to-linked-list/1

n = 5
arr = [1,2,3,4,5]
Output:
1 2 3 4 5
Explanation: Linked list for the given array will be 1->2->3->4->5.

https://practice.geeksforgeeks.org/problems/introduction-to-linked-list/1

Node* constructLL(vector<int>& arr) {
    Node *head;
    Node *temp=new Node(arr[0]);
    head=temp;
    for(int i=1;i<arr.size();i++)
    {
        Node *curr=new Node(arr[i]);
        temp->next=curr;
        temp=temp->next;
    }
    return head;
}

Insertion at the beg: O(1)
Insertion at the end: O(N)

Delete a Node in Single Linked List
https://practice.geeksforgeeks.org/problems/delete-a-node-in-single-linked-list/1

Input: 1 -> 3 -> 4 
       x = 3
Output: 1 -> 3

Node* deleteNode(Node *head,int x)
{
    if(head == NULL || head -> next == NULL) return head;
    
    if(x==1){
        head = head-> next;
        return head;
    }
    
    //Your code here
    Node* curr = head -> next;
    Node* prev = head;
    int count = 1;
    
    while(++count != x){
        prev = curr;
        curr = curr -> next;
    }
    
    prev->next = curr->next;
    free(curr);
    return head;
}
TC: O(N)
